  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nBuild a reputation system for known peers. This will add heuristics about peers as to which peers to prioritise for block downloads, which peers to kick/ban based on their past performance/behaviour.\r\n\r\nThis system should be built as general as possible for future upgrade-ability. We therefore want to have the ability to kick/ban peers at a per-protocol level.\r\n\r\nThis will involve not only a peer reputation system, but a new general `NetworkBehaviour` which references a global `ProtocolsHandler` which allows for banning/disconnects on individual libp2p protocols. This may extend to discv5, otherwise a separate rate-limit may be required to be added to our discv5 implementation.\r\n",
