    "body": "Came across another interesting case. If a node loses connectivity during sync, it's syncing chain will fail and try to re-STATUS peers to restart sync. \r\nThe re-STATUS will timeout and the peers will not register as disconnected. \r\n\r\nThe peer manager may want to store number of status messages sent and if the peer doesn't respond after a specific number we should consider them disconnected and/or disconnect from them. \r\n\r\nIn fact we don't have a ping-like protocol to ensure active connections. We can use STATUS messages as ping-like packets and have timeouts determine peer liveness",
